Revision history for Perl extension Text-Pipe-Translate

1.100890  2010-03-30 00:55:43 Europe/Vienna
    - converted the distribution to Dist::Zilla-style

0.05  Thu 2009.10.08 22:29:11 CEST (Marcel Gruenauer <marcel@cpan.org>)
    - re-release with fixed inc::Module::Install::ReadmeMarkdownFromPod

0.04  Mon 2009.10.05 13:15:06 CEST (Marcel Gruenauer <marcel@cpan.org>)
    - fixed Babelfish backend; removing the URL helped
    - Changed dist style and Changes back to standard. People didn't like it -
      the nail that sticks out gets hammered down.
    - Added standard test files; this will also help with CPANTS.
    - Added INSTALL; now generate README and README.mkdn

0.03  Thu, 29 May 2008 12:08:58 -0000 (Marcel Gruenauer <marcel@cpan.org>)
    - set the version to 0.03
    - updated MANIFEST
    - slight fix to documentation
    - updated t/perlcriticrc
    - moved generated documentation of interited methods to after documentation
      of this class' methods so the manpage is more readable
    - t/01_babelfish.t: Text::Pipe doesn't export pipe() anymore, it's called
      PIPE() now
    - .shipit: fixed svk.tagpattern

0.02  Fri, 16 Nov 2007 07:32:18 -0000 (Marcel Gruenauer <marcel@cpan.org>)
    - set the version to 0.02
    - added Twitter step to .shipit
    - removed comment from Makefile.PL
    - re-generated and re-released now that Module-Install-Template uses
      Data::Dumper instead of YAML; there were CPAN testers failure reports

